1
00:00:04,087 --> 00:00:08,897
One Bengali poet, 
he expresses that

2
00:00:11,203 --> 00:00:13,818
human being
is higher than God.

3
00:00:14,057 --> 00:00:17,408
[Human Higher than God]

4
00:00:18,123 --> 00:00:21,157
Like a Bengali humanist,

5
00:00:21,157 --> 00:00:25,869
“Human being is higher
conception than God”,

6
00:00:26,361 --> 00:00:32,867
and we will say, “Yes, yes!
The aprākṛta-līlā of Kṛṣṇa,

7
00:00:32,928 --> 00:00:35,802
the humanlike pastimes of Kṛṣṇa,

8
00:00:35,864 --> 00:00:40,256
are higher than the God concept.”

9
00:00:42,464 --> 00:00:46,366
That’s why Saraswatī Ṭhākur
liked Godhead,

10
00:00:46,793 --> 00:00:51,062
because ‘God’, we know,
it sounds very abstract,

11
00:00:51,062 --> 00:00:52,215
God …

12
00:00:53,930 --> 00:01:02,245
In some old cartoons from the 50s,
I remember,

13
00:01:02,678 --> 00:01:06,018
where—
interesting as a side point—

14
00:01:06,018 --> 00:01:08,667
the devil always looks like Lenin.

15
00:01:09,855 --> 00:01:12,570
He looks exactly like Lenin.

16
00:01:13,143 --> 00:01:16,518
That’s how, what, the devil looks like,
he’s Lenin.

17
00:01:16,518 --> 00:01:19,046
Just … bald head, and a goatee.

18
00:01:21,291 --> 00:01:25,038
But God would sometimes
be this big …

19
00:01:25,038 --> 00:01:30,829
this, like, a big throne,
with just sparks.

20
00:01:32,152 --> 00:01:33,651
Like, no person there,

21
00:01:33,651 --> 00:01:36,630
or if it showed a person,
no face—

22
00:01:37,698 --> 00:01:42,514
they couldn’t bring themselves
to do that.

23
00:01:43,007 --> 00:01:47,232
So God is an abstraction,

24
00:01:48,586 --> 00:01:55,138
like Īśvara, in Bengali;
that’s the Bengali word for God.

25
00:01:56,378 --> 00:01:58,640
When Guru Mahārāj 
is leaving the world

26
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:04,668
and his internal dilemma is
thinking of Mahāprabhu

27
00:02:04,668 --> 00:02:08,842
or Kṛṣṇa, Rādhārāṇī,
Nityānanda, like that,

28
00:02:08,842 --> 00:02:15,684
and one Rāmachandra Purī-like
devotee said,

29
00:02:15,684 --> 00:02:18,585
“Just, you take Īśvara.”

30
00:02:18,677 --> 00:02:20,661
Mahārāj: “Get out!”

31
00:02:21,952 --> 00:02:24,470
Telling him, “Think of God.”

32
00:02:25,644 --> 00:02:27,851
Telling Guru Mahārāj,

33
00:02:32,681 --> 00:02:35,519
like, Rādhārāṇī’s other self,

34
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:37,838
to think of God.

35
00:02:38,634 --> 00:02:41,579
“Nāhi yogī, Gopīśvara.”

36
00:02:42,236 --> 00:02:49,234
The Vraja-gopīs tell,
“We’re not yogis, Gopīśvara.

37
00:02:50,552 --> 00:02:57,231
Who are you? Yogīśvara, or
aren’t you also known as Gopīśvara,

38
00:02:58,819 --> 00:03:01,331
the lord of the gopis?”

39
00:03:01,454 --> 00:03:04,085
That Īśvara; Gopīśvara.

40
00:03:04,407 --> 00:03:06,145
Not just Īśvara.

41
00:03:06,345 --> 00:03:09,168
īśvaraḥ paramaḥ kṛṣṇaḥ 
[Bs: 5.1].

42
00:03:09,168 --> 00:03:13,295
Which Kṛṣṇa? Dvārakā Kṛṣṇa?
Mathurā Kṛṣṇa?

43
00:03:13,295 --> 00:03:15,169
Vṛndāvan Kṛṣṇa?

44
00:03:15,169 --> 00:03:18,067
Anādir ādir govindaḥ:

45
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:28,019
Govinda. Go-vin-da. Who can
satisfy the senses of everyone,

46
00:03:28,019 --> 00:03:31,870
give joy, Kṛṣṇa.
We were talking today …

47
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:37,971
He’s giving sense pleasure 
to everyone.

48
00:03:37,971 --> 00:03:41,679
viśveṣām anurañjanena janayann
ānandam indīvara-

49
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:48,295
śreṇī-śyāmala-komalair upanayann
ańgair anańgotsavam 
[Cc. Adi: 4.224]

50
00:03:48,295 --> 00:03:50,389
Anaṅga-utsav,

51
00:03:50,389 --> 00:03:54,778
who’s form is a festival,
feast for the eyes.

52
00:03:54,827 --> 00:03:57,391
The beautiful form of Kṛṣṇa.

53
00:03:57,406 --> 00:03:59,232
Acintya-guṇa-svarūpaḿ.

54
00:03:59,232 --> 00:04:02,941
yaḿ śyāmasundaram
achintya-guṇa-svarūpaḿ 
[Bs: 5.38]

55
00:04:02,941 --> 00:04:05,615
the inconceivable form.

56
00:04:05,615 --> 00:04:10,080
Then what are we doing,
trying to conceive these things?

57
00:04:11,339 --> 00:04:18,019
Is it not a type of madness, to try
and conceive the inconceivable?

58
00:04:18,469 --> 00:04:21,500
Say, what do you do
when you enter a country

59
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:25,272
and they want you to fill out
on the immigration form

60
00:04:25,272 --> 00:04:27,295
your occupation?

61
00:04:27,295 --> 00:04:31,514
My occupation is conceiving
the inconceivable,

62
00:04:31,514 --> 00:04:33,813
that is my occupation.

63
00:04:33,813 --> 00:04:36,684
What is your occupation?

64
00:04:37,435 --> 00:04:41,473
We need more people to
specialise in the impossible.

65
00:04:41,735 --> 00:04:44,783
So Guru Mahārāj would say,
“Are we fools

66
00:04:44,783 --> 00:04:47,548
on a wild goose chase?

67
00:04:47,641 --> 00:04:51,413
Is it not absurd
from a particular point of view,

68
00:04:51,413 --> 00:04:55,018
the finite trying to capture
the Infinite?”

69
00:04:56,097 --> 00:05:01,301
That’s why he says, “If you think
you can understand everything

70
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:03,632
about Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

71
00:05:03,632 --> 00:05:06,086
you want to understand
every last detail

72
00:05:06,086 --> 00:05:07,817
and you’ve got 
every book available,”

73
00:05:07,817 --> 00:05:11,462
he said, “then you would be
another Infinite.”

74
00:05:11,617 --> 00:05:12,870
That’s Guru Mahārāj’s response,

75
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:16,015
“Then you would be 
another Infinite;

76
00:05:16,015 --> 00:05:19,768
then you’d be adhokṣaja too.”

77
00:05:21,003 --> 00:05:26,760
janmādy asya yato ’nvayād itarataś
chārtheṣv abhijñaḥ svarāṭ 
[SB: 1.1.1].

78
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:29,936
As they say, 
“God only knows.”

79
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:35,128
That’s true, 
God only knows.

80
00:05:36,410 --> 00:05:39,107
And maybe there are things
He doesn’t know.

81
00:05:40,030 --> 00:05:45,661
Who’s omniscient,
He can’t estimate the love

82
00:05:45,661 --> 00:05:49,058
of Rādhārāṇī, the depth of that,

83
00:05:49,058 --> 00:05:53,003
how much love His devotees have
is astonishing to Him.

84
00:05:53,003 --> 00:05:57,400
How beautiful He is, 
He cannot estimate.

